# F: Drive Workspace

This machine uses **F:** for development. **Do not use C:** for temp files, caches, NuGet, AppData, or build artifacts.

## Paths

| Purpose | Path |
|---------|------|
| Project root | `F:\Coding\windeffects` |
| Builds / output | `F:\Coding\windeffects\Build\` |
| Toolchain cache | `F:\Coding\windeffects\.toolchain\` |
| Build temp | `F:\Coding\windeffects\Build\Temp` |
| SDK / DB cache | `F:\Coding\windeffects\Build\Database\` |
| User temp (shell) | `F:\DevCache\temp` |

## Rules for agents and tooling

- Assume **C: is full or unused** — never suggest writing to `%LOCALAPPDATA%`, `%TEMP%`, or `C:\Users\...` on C:
- Run builds via `.\we.ps1 build` (sets `WE_PROJECT_ROOT`, `LOCALAPPDATA`, `TEMP`, `NUGET_*` on F:)
- Close `WindeffectsEditor.exe` before linking DLLs (`LNK1168` = file locked by running editor)
- IgniteBT redirects toolchain paths in `BuildEnvironment.Configure()` — prefer `BuildEnvironment.ResolveLocalAppData()` / `ResolveTemp()` over `Environment.GetFolderPath(SpecialFolder.LocalApplicationData)` when choosing write locations
